Description: MiniOS session management utility
 A utility for managing MiniOS persistent sessions from within
 the running system. Provides both command-line and graphical
 interfaces for viewing, creating, activating, deleting, and cleaning up sessions.
 .
 This package includes two components:
  * minios-session-cli: Command-line interface for session operations
  * minios-session-manager: GTK3 graphical interface that uses the CLI
 .
 Features:
  * List all available sessions with detailed information
  * View current active session
  * Create new sessions with choice of persistence mode (native, dynfilefs, raw)
  * Activate sessions for next boot
  * Delete old or unused sessions
  * Automatic cleanup of sessions older than specified days
  * Filesystem compatibility detection and mode restrictions
  * Support for all three session types: native, dynfilefs, and raw
  * Both CLI and GUI interfaces
  * Support for both JSON and legacy configuration formats